  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed and a screening sensitivity study was conducted to rank input parameters by influence on the hemolysis index — however all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). The screening sensitivity exercise identified rotational speed and gap clearance as dominant drivers of hemolysis variance; these findings informed the Monte Carlo sampling bounds but were not sufficient to close any credibility gap. Decision: Accepted pending risk mitigation commitments.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
